Text.SourceString: <portrait=annoyed>Is everything okay with your cabin?//<portrait=happy>Oh, good.//<portrait=normal>How do you like the island so far?
Wow! That’s great to hear.
That’s great to hear! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.
I see. Don’t get discouraged! I hope you find what you’re looking for here.
For sure! I hope you find what you’re looking for here, <PlayerName>$player</>.//We’re certainly happy to have you.
If you’re on the way to the dumpster, will you take some of my recycling and drop it off, please?
No worries, if you can’t.//<portrait=concerned>I’m just so swamped today.
I taught <NpcName>Archie</> to bring back things that don’t look like they belong when he plays in the forest.
I was hoping he’d bring back trash and empty bottles.//<portrait=annoyed>But instead he brought home a lot of “shiny rocks” because they “didn’t look like they belong.”
I taught <NpcName>Archie</> to bring back things that don’t look like they belong when he plays in the forest.
I was hoping he’d bring back trash and empty bottles.//<portrait=annoyed>But instead he brought home a lot of “shiny rocks” because they “didn’t look like they belong.”
I don’t have enough land to plant large vegetables, like pumpkins.
Maybe, when I have a chance, I’ll think about expanding my garden a little bit.//<portrait=concerned>But right now, it’s just not a good time.
I was just chatting with <NpcName>Jack</> about starting a small vegetable garden.
We all can chip in our time and energy, and we can take what we need from the garden.//<portrait=happy>Sort of like a community garden, yes.
I wish <NpcName>Archie</> would bring in less dirt from the forest.//<portrait=normal>He sees things on the ground and they’re suddenly “treasures.”
*sighs* The house is turning into a treasure trove of moldy rocks.
Herbs are easy to grow.//As long as you don’t overwater them, they basically grow themselves.
You probably have more gardening tips than I do.
Jam makes a great gift.//I make sure to pack some jars for <NpcName>Joko</>’s family every time he goes to visit them.
You can make any fruit into jam, as long as you have some of those preserves jars on your farm.
Making a cabinet is easier than you think. It just takes a lot of time.
How are you today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Tuesday is a workday for us. Judging from your boots, that seems to be the case for you too!
The hardest thing to craft, for me, would probably be a nice wall clock.
Have you watched the weather channel today?
Hot Summer days are best spent eating freshly harvested melons.//<portrait=happy>My nephew <NpcName>Surya</> and <NpcName>Millie</> both love them too.
Too bad you can’t plant them year-round, though.
*singing in a foreign language*
Favorite fruit? Hmm…//I have to go with melon.
You can tell how sweet a melon is by pushing your finger on the round spot where the vine was attached.//It should release a sweet scent.
Typically, it takes me two to three days to complete a project.//<portrait=happy>So it would be wise for you to plan ahead before committing to one.
<NpcName>Joko</> and I usually spend our Saturday mornings at the community center, doing yoga.
It’s a great way to socialize.
Making a cabinet is easier than you think.//It just takes a lot of time.
How are you today, <PlayerName>$player</>?
You can make any fruit into jam, as long as you have some of those preserves jars on your farm.
We’re closed today…
It’s not urgent, is it?

Clocks are fun to make.//Don’t get me wrong, some of them are hard to craft, but they’re fun regardless.
You need to have enough money before we can start a project.
With all that land you have, farming can be a good way to make some fast money.

As carpenters, <NpcName>Joko</> and I rely heavily on furniture sales.//<portrait=normal>Getting a project is a great way to make some cash because we’re paid up front, but let’s face it!//<portrait=concerned>Large projects don’t come around often.
We live next to a forest, and steps away from the beach.//<portrait=happy>I assure you, <PlayerName>$player</>. For me, life can’t get any better than this.

On top of that, you also need to provide the building materials.

On top of that, you also need to provide the building materials.
It’s Friday again.//We have yoga in front of the community center tomorrow...if it isn't raining, that is.
We live next to a forest, and steps away from the beach.//<portrait=happy>I assure you, <PlayerName>$player</>. For me, life can’t get any better than this.
Clocks are fun to make.//Don’t get me wrong, some of them are hard to craft, but they’re fun regardless.
The shop is going to be closed tomorrow.//We're heading down to the community center in the morning.
I’m going to relax and work on my flexibility.
<NpcName>Archie</> loves playing with <NpcName>Taco</>.//<portrait=concerned>I just hope he isn’t bothering <NpcName>Bree</> too much.
I hope you’re doing well today, <PlayerName>$player</>.
You need to have enough money before we can start a project.//We require payment up front.
Are you enjoying your Sunday so far?
Mine has been good. Thank you for asking.
I think I’m going to make some pies for dinner tonight.
I pulled a muscle on Saturday, trying to stretch.
My leg still feels a bit funny now…//But hopefully it will go away soon.
Do you have any projects for me?
Well, if you ever need a barn or even a pet house, you know where to find me.
Some smaller items, like a doghouse or a shipping crate, can be finished on the same day.
We always have those in stock because of how popular they are.//So, all I need to do is put it together.
Not all woodwork is complicated.//There are some simple things that you can make yourself.
I can teach you how to make some of them, but it would be safer to buy the plans.
On a slow day like this, I can make two or three shipping crates.
But when I take on some projects, I don’t usually craft. I try not to strain myself.
I guarantee I’ll sleep great tonight after all the stretching.
I post help requests on the bulletin board several times a year and the people here seem to want to help.
It’s bamboo shoot season!
I have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some Spring vegetables.
It’s bamboo shoot season!
I have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some Spring vegetables.
I gathered a lot of bamboo shoots over the weekend.//Have you found any yet?
Try checking near <NpcName>Dippa</>’s house. There may be some over there.
I have to check out the lake this weekend and gather some shallots.
I get a bit worried when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.
Sometimes he only wants to eat one or two kinds of food for weeks.//<portrait=happy>Good thing he has a healthy appetite for outdoor activity, though.
Hmm… Maybe I am overthinking this a bit.
I hardly noticed that it’s Fall already, what with all the work to prepare for the Harvest Festival.
Exciting, isn’t it?!
I guess you can call it a hobby.//I use the leftover logs to make wall clocks in my spare time.
<NpcName>Archie</> found a pair of old boots near the cave yesterday and brought them home.
And that’s just one of his “findings.”
It’s probably not a good time to start planting pumpkins, huh?
Doesn’t it take a while for pumpkins to grow?//I’m afraid if you start now, you might not be able to harvest them in time.
*singing a Winter carol*
I get a bit worried when <NpcName>Archie</> gets picky about his food.
Doesn’t it take a while for pumpkins to grow?//I’m afraid if you start now, you might not be able to harvest them in time.
Hmm… Maybe I am overthinking this a bit.
Oh, you poor thing. It must be so cold outside!
Take a seat and warm up.
Oh, you poor thing. It must be so cold outside!
Take a seat and warm up.
Frostbite is a real thing, <PlayerName>$player</>. You be careful, okay?//Keep those socks on and your feet dry at all times.
Frostbite is a real thing, <PlayerName>$player</>. You be careful, okay?//Keep those socks on and your feet dry at all times.
Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?
Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine that’s good for your health.
I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang around, though.
Is everything okay? No leaks, I hope?
Try not to stand in the rain too long, <PlayerName>$player</>.//I can’t imagine that’s good for your health.
I’m a bit busy. Please feel free to hang around, though.
My hometown doesn’t get snow. So this is all new to me.//Even though I’ve lived here almost my whole life, I’m still not used to it yet.
I can’t wait for Spring.//There aren’t many options for fresh flowers this time of year.
What’s Winter without little snow, right?
What’s Winter without little snow, right?
Hot milk sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time for groceries, I suppose.
Hot milk sounds good right now. It’s too bad we ran out.//<portrait=concerned>Time for groceries, I suppose.
Good morning!
The best part of the day is the morning mist, don’t you think?
Keeping these herbs healthy is not as easy as it looks.//It took me a couple of months to learn the secret!
I wonder why my celery keeps wilting.
I can take your order in the shed in a minute.//Do you need anything urgent?
Welcome! I have no projects right now, so if you have any building upgrades to work on, we can start first thing tomorrow morning.
Just write your request in the register, and <NPCName>Joko</> and I will be on our way.
Are you looking for anything in particular?
I’m so glad <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give out plastic bags.//There is no reason we can’t just shove fruit and veggies into our own bags.
There’s already too much plastic in the world.//<portrait=normal>The least we can do is to use as little as possible. Reuse the containers, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I don’t think I could live at the beach, like <NpcName>Sunny</> does.//<portrait=normal>The sun is always so intense over there.
It’s great to be in the sun every once in a while, but all the time? I don’t think so//I need my cool breeze.
I almost cut my finger off chopping wood one time, and all <NpcName>Charles</> did was bandage it up.//<portrait=concerned>He didn’t even give me a tetanus shot.
He told me my vaccinations were up to date, and that was it.//I don’t know how to feel about that.
The bad thing about the shed being connected to the house is the excessive noise.
We do most of our woodworking outdoors, but we still do some of it inside, you know.//So you can imagine how that can be distracting for the family.
We use dovetail joints on all our furniture.//It’s the strongest joint, and the design is aesthetically pleasing.
You can still stay inside your cabin tonight, even if you choose to upgrade it.//We don’t usually start working until morning.
I don’t think <NpcName>Taco</> likes our house very much. Every time he comes in, he goes right back out.//I think it might be too noisy for him.
<NpcName>Taco</> is probably used to a mansion, anyway.
Don’t worry about your boots! No need to take them off.
What brought you here so late, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Have you had dinner? We have some leftovers, if you’d like.
There are so many channels. Two would be just fine.//This many feels very overwhelming.
I should just read my book.
It’s nice of you to visit, <PlayerName>$player</>!
If you want to look at our furniture collection, please come back tomorrow.//I should be in the shed, and I can show it to you.
Please, help yourself!
I found some wasabi earlier. Is it even in season?
Do you know that white oak is the easiest wood to bend?//My father told me that.
It allows me to make some oddly designed furniture.
More people should make a habit of picking up trash and throwing it away.//Even if it’s not their trash to begin with.
Imagine what we could achieve if most people did that.
What time is the yoga going to start today?
I got a bit of a warm-up before my yoga session. I feel very awake now.
I would like to see more classes held. It’s a beautiful way to bond with the community.
We never miss a class. You can most likely find us here on Saturdays.
It’s great to see you out and about!
Are you here for the yoga class too, <PlayerName>$player</>?
The mayor? I saw him going toward town earlier.
I’m not positive, though. I was a bit preoccupied.
I’m not here to see the mayor.//<portrait=happy>There are plenty of wild vegetables around here. Foraging them is my favorite activity.
You should check the lake for mushrooms!//There were plenty over there the other week.
Plenty of wild vegetables today!
I enjoy gathering wild vegetables.//It’s always exciting to see what nature has to offer.
It’s a nice break to come here after work once in a while.
Plenty of wild vegetables today!
These can last us the whole week.
He's a very nifty florist. I came here for a bouquet.
I think it’s admirable that <NpcName>Ben</> tries not to consume animal products.//So, keep that in mind when you’re choosing gifts for him.
<NpcName>Ben</> has called me “Doodz” several times. I don’t quite understand.//There’s so much to learn from the youth…
Oh, he called you that too! What a fun coincidence.
I don't know what type of fish are in this lake, <NpcName>Archie</>.//Your uncle might be able to help with that.
